urlText: Trackwork between Bondi Junction and Central
content:
Monday 1 to Thursday 4 February
  • Nightly from 9.40pm until 1.30am, buses replace trains between Bondi Junction and Central.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Waterfall or Cronulla and the City Circle.
  • Trackwork buses do not leave from Martin Place Station.
  • From Martin Place, Sydney Buses services run to:
    • Bondi Junction from Elizabeth St
    • Kings Cross and Edgecliff from Park St, Town Hall
    • Central from Castlereagh St
    • or you can also catch the light rail to Town Hall and Central.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
20T4: Bondi Junction, Edgecliff, Kings Cross, then Central and return (bypassing Martin Place)
23T4: Bondi Junction, then Town Hall and return
324: City, Walsh Bay to Watsons Bay via Old South Head Rd
- Town Hall (Park St), Kings Cross, Edgecliff and return
325: City, Walsh Bay to Watsons Bay via Vaucluse Rd
- Town Hall (Park St), Kings Cross, Edgecliff and return
subtitle: Trackwork between Bondi Junction and Central

urlText: Trackwork between Cronulla, Waterfall and Central
content:
Saturday 20 and Sunday 21 February
  • Buses replace trains between Cronulla, Waterfall and Central. Some buses start and end at Redfern.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Bondi Junction and Central.
  • If you are travelling to T8 Airport & South Line stations, change at Central or catch bus 7AT4 to Wolli Creek and change for a T8 Airport & South Line train.
  • If you are travelling from the City to:
    • Tempe, Arncliffe, Banksia, Rockdale, Kogarah, Carlton or Allawah change at Redfern for an all-stations bus.
    • all other Illawarra or South Coast Line stations change at Central for express or limited stop buses.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
1T4: Cronulla, then all stations to Caringbah then Central and return
1AT4: Kirrawee, then all stations to Miranda then Central and return
2T4: Waterfall, then all stations to Sutherland then Central and return
2AT4: Sutherland, then all stations to Hurstville then Central and return
3AT4: Hurstville, then Central and return
5AT4: Kogarah, Rockdale then Redfern and return
6AT4: Cronulla, then all stations to Sutherland, Hurstville, then all stations to Rockdale, Tempe, Sydenham then Redfern and return
7T4: Penshurst all to Wolli Creek and return
7AT4: Hurstville, then all stations to Redfern and return
17T4: Banksia Station Shuttle (Princes Hwy to Railway St and return)
subtitle: Trackwork between Cronulla, Waterfall and Central

urlText: Trackwork between Dapto and Central, and between Port Kembla and Wollongong
content:
Saturday 20 and Sunday 21 February
  • Buses replace trains between Dapto and Central, and between Port Kembla and Wollongong.
  • Trains run to a changed timetable between Bomaderry and Kiama, and between Kiama and Dapto.
  • South Coast Line trackwork buses do not stop at Wolli Creek. If you are travelling to T8 Airport & South Line stations, please change at Central for a T8 Airport & South Line train.
  • Some late night and early morning buses will extend to Kiama.
  • Plan your trip before you travel for up-to-date information.
Bus routes
1SC: Bomaderry, then all stations to Kiama and return
27SC: Port Kembla, then all stations to Wollongong and return
33SC: Kiama, then all stations to Dapto and return
43SC: Dapto, Wollongong, North Wollongong, Sutherland then Central and return
44SC: Dapto all to Thirroul, Sutherland then Central and return
45SC: Wollongong, then all stations to Waterfall, Sutherlandthen Central and return (except Otford)
48SC: Helensburgh Station, Helensburgh (town) then Otford Station and return
subtitle: Trackwork between Dapto and Central, and between Port Kembla and Wollongong
